15 Aug 2020 15:05






Hello author,

I'mhere...

Return


This is kind of fun and there's definitely something here but the sum total of the details is just lacking a bit of cohesion for me. It doesn't quite  if you will.

For starters, stuff like



approximately 560.5km in diameter.
附加记录：    

You're talking about an area, and then to say approximately but go to the  at this level seems silly.

There's just a general lack of precision in the language throughout this piece that, if corrected, would cement this a lot. The big table in the Description is more or less useless with all the black boxes. All you wanted to convey was which ones are neutralized, you didn't need to gum up the screen with a big patch of redacted info.



Three minutes after a boxer has entered its region of the ocean, SCP-5916 will become hostile and immediately accelerate towards the intruder at speeds in excess of Mach 20.
附加记录：    

Three minutes? Why get specific here? The fact that it's 3 minutes doesn't seem to actually matter. You can just say  and we come out the same on the other side.

I'd also point out that moving through the water at Mach 20 would kill every living thing in the ocean across the entirety of planet Earth. Mach 20 is so inconceivably fast that I'm not sure you understand. Traveling at Mach 20 would allow a person to circumnavigate the entire planet in less than 2 hours. I think you're going for  here, and in your rush to convey that you've introduced something so hyperbolic my suspension of disbelief is shattered.



Dr. Yung: You mean 5916-9?

5916-10: Little punk thought he could take me with a sucker punch. Showed him.
附加记录：    

How does this -10 know who -9 is? That's our designation not theirs.

Too many errors here; this could do with a few more passes for critique and SPG. You're 80-90% of the way there in my estimation.








